@prefix narr: <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#> .
@prefix xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .

GRAPH <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Digest_PackagingEntitlement> {
  <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Digest_PackagingEntitlement> a narr:Digest ;
    narr:digestOf <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#PackagingEntitlement> ;
    narr:childCount "20"^^xsd:integer ;
    narr:generatedFrom "7f8290da0a1a14cf6b197a7c4e4a551e85f737a7" ;
    narr:narration """This hub packages aswritten's capability tiers and the mechanisms that gate them. The mainline runs Free → Expert → Team → Org. [Free is read-only](narr:Position_FreeTierReadOnly_DesignSession) — perspectives load but nothing saves — which is the deliberate gate driving the first upgrade. [Expert is single-stream](narr:Position_ExpertSingleStreamNoGitBranching): memories commit to main, no PRs or branches by default, with [synchronous self-review after every save](narr:Position_ExpertTierSyncReview); it functions as [a feeder and near paid-demo](narr:Position_ExpertTierAsPaidDemo) rather than a standalone business. [Team adds multi-user contribution](narr:Position_TeamTierGitHubBranch) to one worldview, and [the sales call is simultaneously onboarding and first extraction](narr:Narrative_SalesCallIsOnboarding) — no separate setup deliverable. [Org bundles three capabilities](narr:Position_OrgTierThreeCapabilities): sandboxed internal AI, external agent deployments, and EDOs. A recurring reframe (Jul 2025, Apr 2026) holds that [GitHub connectivity × team size are the real axes](narr:Narrative_TierAxisGitHubTeamSize), with tiers as packaging on top. Mechanically, gating works via [compile returning plan-level instruction sets](narr:Position_PlanGatedInstructionsFromCompile), not separate tools. The [admin tier was eliminated](narr:Position_AdminTierEliminated) (Mar 2026). A newer reframe (Apr 2026) repositions the Team/Org boundary as [whose infrastructure owns the coordination plane](narr:Narrative_TierReframeInfrastructure). [SMS tier placement](narr:Position_SMSEnterpriseOnlyLeaning) remains a recorded leaning, not a decision.""" ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_OrgTierAgentDeploymentValue> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_PlanGatedInstructions> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_SalesCallIsOnboarding> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_TierAxisGitHubTeamSize> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_TierReframeInfrastructure> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_PlanGatedQuote> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_ScarletExpertGitHubQuote> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_ScarletTeamWithoutGitHubQuote> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_TeamTierOnboardingQuote> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_AdminTierEliminated> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_CompileReturnsPlanGatedInstructions> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_ExpertSingleStreamNoGitBranching> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_ExpertTierAsPaidDemo> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_ExpertTierSyncReview> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_FreeTierReadOnly_DesignSession> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_OrgTierThreeCapabilities> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_PlanGatedInstructionsFromCompile> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_SMSEnterpriseOnlyLeaning> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_TeamPlanAtLaunch> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_TeamTierGitHubBranch> ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "Free tier: read-only. Can load and use perspectives. Cannot save memories. Cannot review. This is the capability gate that drives the Free→Expert upgrade." ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_FreeTierReadOnly_DesignSession> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "Expert plan: memories save to main by default. No PRs, no branches, no merge-via-MCP (task-171 moved below the line), no concurrent branch handling, no rebase bugs. Single-stream worldview — every remember updates the one worldview." ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_ExpertSingleStreamNoGitBranching> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "In the Expert case, it actually makes most sense to always commit to main. In the single-user case, it usually makes sense to commit to main by default and to have synchronous review." ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_ScarletExpertGitHubQuote> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "In Team without GitHub, a user reviews their own memories, and we're just working against the same thing. That is decidedly not as clean as with GitHub, but that's the whole point." ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_ScarletTeamWithoutGitHubQuote> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "The Expert tier specifically functions as a feeder — and, in sales conversations, as something close to a paid demo, since many prospects use it that way." ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_ExpertTierAsPaidDemo> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "Feature gating mechanism: compile returns different instructions based on authenticated plan level. Not separate tool sets — different prompts guiding agent behavior per plan. Remember exists at all plan levels but returns upgrade prompt on free plan." ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_PlanGatedInstructionsFromCompile> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "Admin tier eliminated. Everything that was admin-only (stories, register, refract, memories/source) is now either an org-repo Claude Code skill or just 'read the files.' No separate admin tier needed. Ontology (raw access) moves to Team/Org tier." ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_AdminTierEliminated> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "The distinction between Team and Org tiers is the ownership of the coordination plane. Org tier owns their own Front-equivalent stack; Team tier are guests on Scarlet's managed infrastructure." ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_TierReframeInfrastructure> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "We don't know yet how this maps to tiers... I don't want to make that decision right now." ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_SMSEnterpriseOnlyLeaning> ] ;
    narr:variation [ narr:text "The Team/Org boundary has two competing framings: capability bundle (three Org capabilities) vs. infrastructure ownership (who owns the coordination plane) — the Apr 2026 reframe may supersede the capability-count framing without explicitly retiring it." ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_TierReframeInfrastructure> ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_OrgTierThreeCapabilities> ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_OrgTierAgentDeploymentValue> ] ;
    narr:variation [ narr:text "Tiers-as-packaging vs. tiers-as-real-gates: the GitHub × team-size axis framing (Jul 2025) holds tiers are a layer on top of capability dimensions, which sits in tension with the compile-returns-plan-gated-instructions mechanism that treats plan level as the authoritative gate." ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_TierAxisGitHubTeamSize> ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_PlanGatedInstructionsFromCompile> ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_PlanGatedInstructions> ] ;
    narr:variation [ narr:text "SMS tier placement is a recorded leaning toward enterprise-only but explicitly not a decision — an open variable that could shift tier boundaries." ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_SMSEnterpriseOnlyLeaning> ] ;
    narr:variation [ narr:text "Expert as paid-demo/feeder (May 2026) reframes Expert's commercial role away from standalone value, which qualifies whether Expert needs to stand on its own merits or only needs to convert." ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_ExpertTierAsPaidDemo> ] ;
    narr:variation [ narr:text "Team plan launch requires manual flow to work even without full automation (task-169 repo transfer below the line) — a deliberate scope constraint that leaves the tier partially incomplete at launch." ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_TeamPlanAtLaunch> ] ;
    narr:writer "anthropic/claude-sonnet-4.6" .
}